==Tatar==

===Etymology===
English [[athel#English|athel]], noble, Old English ''aethelu'', nobility.
Common Germanic: Swedish ''ädel'', Deutsch ''adel''. Also Scots Gaelic ''uasal''.

#''Etymological spelling:'' '''athel
#''Phonetic spellings:'' '''asil''', '''adel'''
  
===Adjective===

#[[athel#English|athel]], [[atheling]], [[noble]]. The word ''athel'' (or ''adel''), is in many Tatar proper names, as '''Athel'''herei, noble hero; '''Athel'''han, noble ruler(head);

